/*
 * Localizable.strings (English)
 *
 * Two kinds of entries live here:
 *
 * 1. Keys for programmatic strings constructed via String(localized:). These
 *    are namespaced (error.*, food_scan.*, …) — the Swift call references
 *    the key directly, so renaming a key requires renaming the Swift call.
 *
 * 2. Verbatim SwiftUI Text() strings. SwiftUI's Text initializer treats a
 *    string literal as a LocalizedStringKey, so any literal you've already
 *    written in a Text() will be looked up here if a matching entry exists.
 *    Add entries here as you localize each screen — missing keys fall back
 *    to the literal, so partial coverage is safe.
 *
 * To add a new locale: duplicate the en.lproj folder (e.g. fr.lproj) and
 * translate the values. Xcode + xcodegen pick up sibling .lproj folders
 * automatically.
 */

